1. #fdisk -l

2. Create a folder
- #sudo mkdir /media/name_of_device

3. Edit  /etc/fstab
- /dev/sdb1 /mnt/sdb1 vfat defaults 0 0

4. mounta -a

Some tools will mount external device by it own:
- EnCase
- C.A.IN.E
- Ewfmount
- Xmount

////////////////////////////////WINDOWS IMAGE MOUNTING////////////////////////////

1. Arsenal Image Mounter (AIM)
Free tool that can mount various formts including split files and Encases files.

2. FTK Imager
Offers image mounting but no latest Encases files

3. OSFMount

4. P2-eXplorer
